3) Option (a) is more general - it simply states that Travis would continue driving while trying to make conversation. This is a subset of the scenario presented in option (b).

5) Thus, by the laws of probability, option (a) is more likely: Travis would continue driving while trying to make conversation with the woman.

The correct answer is (a).
